    <main>
      <div class="recipe-card">
        <h2>Red Lentil Hummus</h2>
        
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>125g red lentils</li>
          <li>1 lemon</li>
          <li>4 tbsp olive oil, plus extra for drizzling</li>
          <li>2 tbsp tahini</li>
          <li>1 tsp lazy garlic or 2 garlic cloves, crushed</li>
          <li>Paprika</li>
          <li>Salt and black pepper</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Tip the red lentils into a saucepan and cover with boiling water</li>
          <li>Bring to the boil, reduce the heat and simmer for about 10 minutes, until soft</li>
          <li>Drain the lentils and add them to a bowl</li>
          <li>Halve the lemon and squeeze in the juice</li>
          <li>Add the olive oil, tahini, garlic and salt</li>
          <li>Mix everything thoroughly until well combined</li>
          <li>Add a splash of water to loosen, if necessary</li>
          <li>Adjust the seasoning to taste</li>
          <li>To serve: Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with paprika</li>
        </ol>

        <p class="source">Source: Speedy! BOSH</p>
      </div>
